### Rate Limit Headers

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/docs/api-reference/v1/rate-limit.mdx

Information about the rate limit headers returned in API responses.

```APIDOC
## Rate Limit Information

### Description
This section details the headers provided in API responses to inform consumers about their current rate limit status.

### Method
All API endpoints

### Endpoint
N/A (Applies to all responses)

### Headers
- **X-RateLimit-Limit** (integer) - The maximum number of requests allowed in the current window.
- **X-RateLimit-Remaining** (integer) - The number of requests remaining in the current window.
- **X-RateLimit-Reset** (integer) - The UTC epoch seconds timestamp when the rate limit window resets.

### Response Example (Success)
```json
{
  "some_data": "example_response_body"
}
```

### Response Example (Rate Limit Exceeded)
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "too_many_requests",
    "message": "Rate limit exceeded"
  }
}
```

### Error Handling
When the rate limit is exceeded, the API will return a `429 Too Many Requests` status code along with a JSON body indicating the error.
```

