### Endpoint Validation Rules

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/apps/api/v1/README.md

Cal.com API endpoints enforce specific HTTP methods and use Zod for request validation to ensure data integrity.

```APIDOC
## API Endpoint Validation Rules

### Endpoint Behavior
- `/endpoint`: Supports `GET` (list all) and `POST` (create new).
- `/endpoint/id`: Supports `GET` (read), `PATCH` (edit), and `DELETE`.

### Zod Validations
The API uses the `zod` library for request validation. Schemas are often auto-generated from `@calcom/prisma` models and located in `lib/validations/`.

Common validation patterns include:
- `baseApiParams`: Validates the `apiKey` in all requests.
- `queryIdAsString` or `TransformParseInt`: Handles ID parameters from `req.query`.
- `[*]BaseBodyParams`: Omits sensitive fields (like `id`, `userId`) from request bodies during resource creation.
- `[*]Public`: Omits fields not intended for public exposure when returning resources.
- `[*]BodyParams`: Merges `[*]BaseBodyParams` with required parameters.
```

