### Securely Querying User Credentials in Prisma

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/agents/coding-standards.md

Illustrates how to securely fetch user data using Prisma by explicitly excluding sensitive fields like 'key' from the selection. It highlights a common security vulnerability and the correct approach.

```typescript
// ❌ NEVER expose credential keys
const user = await prisma.user.findFirst({
  select: {
    credentials: {
      select: {
        key: true, // ❌ NEVER do this
      }
    }
  }
});

// ✅ Good - Never select credential.key field
const user = await prisma.user.findFirst({
  select: {
    credentials: {
      select: {
        id: true,
        type: true,
        // key field is excluded for security
      }
    }
  }
});
```
